<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 5: ROCKER ARM ASSEMBLY, CAMSHAFT
        ASSEMBLY, TAPPETS AND PUSH RODS - INSTALLATION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>INSTALLATION</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="0">
            <title>CAMSHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the engine in the vertical position, lubricate the camshaft and the camshaft
                    bushings using clean engine oil.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>
                            <emph type="underscr">BE SURE</emph>
                            TO AVOID NICKING OR SCRATCHING CAMSHAFT BUSHINGS WITH CAM LOBES.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Gently slide camshaft assembly into crankcase. Be careful not to damage camshaft
                    bushings.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two (2) thrust plate mounting bolts and tighten to the special torque value.
                    Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e160_131.xml" xrefid="ef1600532">5.32</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Bolts securing timing disk to camgear
                            <emph type="underscr">SHOULD</emph>
                            be replaced every time the timing disk is removed.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install camgear timing disk plate over two (2) dowel pins and tighten bolts to the
                    special torque value (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e160_131.xml" xrefid="ef1600533">5.33</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install idler gears as described in Section 8,
                    <emph type="bold">"TIMING GEAR TRAIN AND FRONT COVER"</emph>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check camshaft gear backlash and camshaft end play as described in Section 8,
                    <emph type="bold">"TIMING GEAR TRAIN AND FRONT COVER".</emph>Specifications must be met.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
